modules.description: Provides functions to serialize and deserialize a Git repository, and to clone a remote repository into a local structure. Works with data types representing repository metadata, object trees, and commit histories. Used to initialize repositories from existing data or fetch content from a remote source.

This module enables key-value store operations within a Git repository, supporting actions like adding, removing, and modifying entries, along with Git-specific tasks such as committing changes and synchronizing with a remote. It operates on a `t` type representing a local Git repository, leveraging commits and serialized states to track modifications. Use cases include managing asynchronous updates with `change_and_push` for atomic commits or syncing later, while handling desynchronization by preserving unpushed changes in serialized form.
